column5: BCG is the only vaccine currently available for the control of TB. Document evidence has established that it provides good protection in children against disseminated TB and TB meningitis.

OPVs are safe and effective and offer long lasting protection against the serotypes which they target. OPV stimulates good mucosal immunity#Comma which is why it is so effective at interrupting transmission of the virus.
Hepatitis B vaccine provides greater than 90% protection to immunized children and adults#Comma for a long duration of time.
There is not yet sufficient evidence on how effective this pentavalent vaccine is compared to the individual vaccines.
